'''''Moskovskaya Komsomolka'''''  was a [[satirical]] newspaper published weekly in [[Russia]] (1999-2001) <ref>http://www.fmradio.ru/news/100-sumerki-off.htm</ref>. The newspaper had a fixed 32 page layout. 

==Presentation==
Founded by [[Boris Berezovsky (businessman)|Boris Berezovsky]] and [[Yevgeny Dodolev]] <ref>http://www.businesspress.ru/newspaper/article_mId_3_aId_3333.html</ref>, it featured [[investigative journalism]] and leaks from sources inside the Russian business world, as well as a large number of  cartoons. Its history saw a number of [[Parody|stunts]]. It published so-called "leaks" from administration officials, including information from whistle-blowers

[[Valeriya Novodvorskaya]] said that it was most provocative newspaper in Russia <ref>http://www.ds.ru/secsot99.htm</ref>.

Although the ''Moskovskaya Komsomolka'' never lost its touches of humor, it soon established itself as a pre-eminent forum for serious journalism. 

The ''Moskovskaya Komsomolka'' writers include:
*[[Dmitrii Bykov]]
*[[Sergey Dorenko]]
*[[Marina Lesko]]
*[[Eduard Limonov]]

